","1282":"1282","1260":"1260","Abt 1280":"circa 1280","14 April 1305":"14 april 1305","1280":"1280","1317":"1317","Altry, Listowel, Kerry, Kerry, Ireland":"Listowel, County Kerry, Ierland","Molahiffe, Kerry, Kerry, Ireland":"Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ierland","Ireland":"Ierland","Kerry, Ireland":"County Kerry, Ierland","Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland":"Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ierland"},"en":{"1262–1336":"1262–1336","1260–1305":"1260–1305","1280–1317":"1280–1317","1282–Male":"1282–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1235–Male":"1235–Deceased","1240–Female":"1240–Deceased","1305":"1305","1336":"1336","1235":"1235","1262":"1262","about 1299":"about 1299","1240":"1240","1282":"1282","1260":"1260","Abt 1280":"about 1280","14 April 1305":"14 April 1305","1280":"1280","1317":"1317","Altry, Listowel, Kerry, Kerry, Ireland":"Listowel, County Kerry, Ireland","Molahiffe, Kerry, Kerry, Ireland":"Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland","Ireland":"Ireland","Kerry, Ireland":"County Kerry, Ireland","Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland":"Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"FitzWilliam","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish (of Norman origin): from Anglo-Norman French <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ (see   Fitz  ) + the personal name   William  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (from Latin <i>filius</i>), used originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same personal name and then conventionalized as a hereditary surname, or short for a surname of which <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ was the first element, for example   Fitzhenry   and   Fitzroy  .","Altered form of English   Fitch  .","German: from a vernacular pet form of the personal name <i>Vinzenz</i> (see   Vincent  ) or <i>Vitus</i> (see   Vito  , compare   Veit  ). Compare also   Fietz  ."]}]},{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ellen FitzWilliam was born in 1262, in Listowel, County Kerry, Ireland, her father, William Fitzelias, was 27 and her mother, Mrs. William Fitzelie Fitzelias, was 23. She married Maurice FitzThomas 2nd Baron of Kerry about 1299. They were the parents of at least 5 sons. She died in 1336, in Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1262–1336":"1262–1336","1260–1305":"1260–1305","1280–1317":"1280–1317","1282–Male":"1282–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1305":"1305","1336":"1336","1235":"1235","1262":"1262","about 1299":"umbes 1299","1240":"1240","1282":"1282","1260":"1260","Abt 1280":"umbes 1280","14 April 1305":"14. aprill 1305","1280":"1280","1317":"1317","Altry, Listowel, Kerry, Kerry, Ireland":"Listowel, County Kerry, Iirimaa","Molahiffe, Kerry, Kerry, Ireland":"Molahiffe, County Kerry, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Kerry, Ireland":"County Kerry, Iirimaa","Molahiffe, County Kerry, Ireland":"Molahiffe, County Kerry, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1262–13